Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} and add @salt{1/2%tsp}. Bring back to
the boil on medium heat.

Add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook
until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat. When hot, add the garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%secs}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g} into the garlic.

Add the @water{150%ml} and stir to combine. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until
the sauce has reduced and thickened slightly, ~{4-5%mins}.

Add the @peas{120%g} to the sauce, then add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at
a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Once the penne is cooked, add to the sauce and stir to coat.

Stir through the @fresh pesto{32%g} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

Serve the pasta in bowls and finish with a sprinkling of the remaining
cheese. Enjoy!